name: Add
description: Adds two values and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Add_Ovf
description: Adds two integers, performs an overflow check, and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Add_Ovf_Un
description: Adds two unsigned integer values, performs an overflow check, and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: And
description: Computes the bitwise AND of two values and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Arglist
description: Returns an unmanaged pointer to the argument list of the current method.

name: Beq
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if two values are equal.

name: Beq_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction (short form) if two values are equal.

name: Bge
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if the first value is greater than or equal to the second value.

name: Bge_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction (short form) if the first value is greater than or equal to the second value.

name: Bge_Un
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if the first value is greater than the second value, when comparing unsigned integer values or unordered float values.

name: Bge_Un_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction (short form) if the first value is greater than the second value, when comparing unsigned integer values or unordered float values.

name: Bgt
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if the first value is greater than the second value.

name: Bgt_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction (short form) if the first value is greater than the second value.

name: Bgt_Un
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if the first value is greater than the second value, when comparing unsigned integer values or unordered float values.

name: Bgt_Un_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction (short form) if the first value is greater than the second value, when comparing unsigned integer values or unordered float values.

name: Ble
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if the first value is less than or equal to the second value.

name: Ble_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction (short form) if the first value is less than or equal to the second value.

name: Ble_Un
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if the first value is less than or equal to the second value, when comparing unsigned integer values or unordered float values.

name: Ble_Un_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction (short form) if the first value is less than or equal to the second value, when comparing unsigned integer values or unordered float values.

name: Blt
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if the first value is less than the second value.

name: Blt_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction (short form) if the first value is less than the second value.

name: Blt_Un
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if the first value is less than the second value, when comparing unsigned integer values or unordered float values.

name: Blt_Un_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction (short form) if the first value is less than the second value, when comparing unsigned integer values or unordered float values.

name: Bne_Un
description: Transfers control to a target instruction when two unsigned integer values or unordered float values are not equal.

name: Bne_Un_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction (short form) when two unsigned integer values or unordered float values are not equal.

name: Box
description: Converts a value type to an object reference (type O).

name: Br
description: Unconditionally transfers control to a target instruction.

name: Br_S
description: Unconditionally transfers control to a target instruction (short form).

name: Break
description: Signals the Common Language Infrastructure (CLI) to inform the debugger that a break point has been tripped.

name: Brfalse
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if value is false, a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic), or zero.

name: Brfalse_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if value is false, a null reference, or zero.

name: Brtrue
description: Transfers control to a target instruction if value is true, not null, or non-zero.

name: Brtrue_S
description: Transfers control to a target instruction (short form) if value is true, not null, or non-zero.

name: Call
description: Calls the method indicated by the passed method descriptor.

name: Call
description: Calls the method indicated by the passed method descriptor.

name: Calli
description: Calls the method indicated on the evaluation stack (as a pointer to an entry point) with arguments described by a calling convention.

name: Callvirt
description: Calls a late-bound method on an object, pushing the return value onto the evaluation stack.

name: Castclass
description: Attempts to cast an object passed by reference to the specified class.

name: Ceq
description: Compares two values. If they are equal, the integer value 1 (int32) is pushed onto the evaluation stack; otherwise 0 (int32) is pushed onto the evaluation stack.

name: Cgt
description: Compares two values. If the first value is greater than the second, the integer value 1 (int32) is pushed onto the evaluation stack; otherwise 0 (int32) is pushed onto the evaluation stack.

name: Cgt_Un
description: Compares two unsigned or unordered values. If the first value is greater than the second, the integer value 1 (int32) is pushed onto the evaluation stack; otherwise 0 (int32) is pushed onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ckfinite
description: Throws ArithmeticException if value is not a finite number.

name: Clt
description: Compares two values. If the first value is less than the second, the integer value 1 (int32) is pushed onto the evaluation stack; otherwise 0 (int32) is pushed onto the evaluation stack.

name: Clt_Un
description: Compares the unsigned or unordered values value1 and value2. If value1 is less than value2, then the integer value 1 (int32) is pushed onto the evaluation stack; otherwise 0 (int32) is pushed onto the evaluation stack.

name: Constrained
description: Constrains the type on which a virtual method call is made.

name: Conv_I
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to native int.

name: Conv_I1
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to int8, then extends (pads) it to int32.

name: Conv_I2
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to int16, then extends (pads) it to int32.

name: Conv_I4
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to int32.

name: Conv_I8
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to int64.

name: Conv_Ovf_I
description: Converts the signed value on top of the evaluation stack to signed native int, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_I1
description: Converts the signed value on top of the evaluation stack to signed int8 and extends it to int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_I1_Un
description: Converts the unsigned value on top of the evaluation stack to signed int8 and extends it to int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_I2
description: Converts the signed value on top of the evaluation stack to signed int16 and extending it to int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_I2_Un
description: Converts the unsigned value on top of the evaluation stack to signed int16 and extends it to int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_I4
description: Converts the signed value on top of the evaluation stack to signed int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_I4_Un
description: Converts the unsigned value on top of the evaluation stack to signed int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_I8
description: Converts the signed value on top of the evaluation stack to signed int64, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_I8_Un
description: Converts the unsigned value on top of the evaluation stack to signed int64, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_I_Un
description: Converts the unsigned value on top of the evaluation stack to signed native int, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_U
description: Converts the signed value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned native int, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_U1
description: Converts the signed value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int8 and extends it to int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_U1_Un
description: Converts the unsigned value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int8 and extends it to int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_U2
description: Converts the signed value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int16 and extends it to int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_U2_Un
description: Converts the signed value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int16 and extends it to int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_U4
description: Converts the signed value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_U4_Un
description: Converts the unsigned value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int32, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_U8
description: Converts the signed value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int64, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_U8_Un
description: Converts the unsigned value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int64, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_Ovf_U_Un
description: Converts the unsigned value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned native int, throwing OverflowException on overflow.

name: Conv_R4
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to float32.

name: Conv_R8
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to float32.

name: Conv_R_Un
description: Converts the unsigned integer value on top of the evaluation stack to float32.

name: Conv_U
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to float32.

name: Conv_U1
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int8, and extends it to int32.

name: Conv_U2
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int16, and extends it to int32.

name: Conv_U4
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int32, and extends it to int32.

name: Conv_U8
description: Converts the value on top of the evaluation stack to unsigned int64, and extends it to int64.

name: Cpblk
description: Copies a specified number bytes from a source address to a destination address.

name: Cpobj
description: Copies the value type located at the address of an object (type &, or native int) to the address of the destination object (type &, or native int).

name: Div
description: Divides two values and pushes the result as a floating-point (type F) or quotient (type int32) onto the evaluation stack.

name: Div_Un
description: Divides two unsigned integer values and pushes the result (int32) onto the evaluation stack.

name: Dup
description: Copies the current topmost value on the evaluation stack, and then pushes the copy onto the evaluation stack.

name: Endfilter
description: Transfers control from the filter clause of an exception back to the Common Language Infrastructure (CLI) exception handler.

name: Endfinally
description: Transfers control from the fault or finally clause of an exception block back to the Common Language Infrastructure (CLI) exception handler.

name: Initblk
description: Initializes a specified block of memory at a specific address to a given size and initial value.

name: Initobj
description: Initializes each field of the value type at a specified address to a null reference or a 0 of the appropriate primitive type.

name: Isinst
description: Tests whether an object reference (type O) is an instance of a particular class.

name: Jmp
description: Exits current method and jumps to specified method.

name: Ldarg
description: Loads an argument (referenced by a specified index value) onto the stack.

name: Ldarg_0
description: Loads the argument at index 0 onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldarg_1
description: Loads the argument at index 1 onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldarg_2
description: Loads the argument at index 2 onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldarg_3
description: Loads the argument at index 3 onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldarg_S
description: Loads the argument (referenced by a specified short form index) onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldarga
description: Load an argument address onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldarga_S
description: Load an argument address, in short form, onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldc_I4
description: Pushes a supplied value of type int32 onto the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldc_I4_0
description: Pushes the integer value of 0 onto the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldc_I4_1
description: Pushes the integer value of 1 onto the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldc_I4_2
description: Pushes the integer value of 2 onto the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldc_I4_3
description: Pushes the integer value of 3 onto the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldc_I4_4
description: Pushes the integer value of 4 onto the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldc_I4_5
description: Pushes the integer value of 5 onto the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldc_I4_6
description: Pushes the integer value of 6 onto the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldc_I4_7
description: Pushes the integer value of 7 onto the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldc_I4_8
description: Pushes the integer value of 8 onto the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldc_I4_M1
description: Pushes the integer value of -1 onto the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldc_I4_S
description: Pushes the supplied int8 value onto the evaluation stack as an int32, short form.

name: Ldc_I4_S
description: Pushes the supplied int8 value onto the evaluation stack as an int32, short form.

name: Ldc_I8
description: Pushes a supplied value of type int64 onto the evaluation stack as an int64.

name: Ldc_R4
description: Pushes a supplied value of type float32 onto the evaluation stack as type F (float).

name: Ldc_R8
description: Pushes a supplied value of type float64 onto the evaluation stack as type F (float).

name: Ldelem
description: Loads the element at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as the type specified in the instruction.

name: Ldelem_I
description: Loads the element with type native int at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as a native int.

name: Ldelem_I1
description: Loads the element with type int8 at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldelem_I2
description: Loads the element with type int16 at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldelem_I4
description: Loads the element with type int32 at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldelem_I8
description: Loads the element with type int64 at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as an int64.

name: Ldelem_R4
description: Loads the element with type float32 at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as type F (float).

name: Ldelem_R8
description: Loads the element with type float64 at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as type F (float).

name: Ldelem_Ref
description: Loads the element containing an object reference at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as type O (object reference).

name: Ldelem_U1
description: Loads the element with type unsigned int8 at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldelem_U2
description: Loads the element with type unsigned int16 at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldelem_U4
description: Loads the element with type unsigned int32 at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as an int32.

name: Ldelema
description: Loads the address of the array element at a specified array index onto the top of the evaluation stack as type & (managed pointer).

name: Ldfld
description: Finds the value of a field in the object whose reference is currently on the evaluation stack.

name: Ldflda
description: Finds the address of a field in the object whose reference is currently on the evaluation stack.

name: Ldftn
description: Pushes an unmanaged pointer (type native int) to the native code implementing a specific method onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldind_I
description: Loads a value of type native int as a native int onto the evaluation stack indirectly.

name: Ldind_I1
description: Loads a value of type int8 as an int32 onto the evaluation stack indirectly.

name: Ldind_I2
description: Loads a value of type int16 as an int32 onto the evaluation stack indirectly.

name: Ldind_I4
description: Loads a value of type int32 as an int32 onto the evaluation stack indirectly.

name: Ldind_I8
description: Loads a value of type int64 as an int64 onto the evaluation stack indirectly.

name: Ldind_R4
description: Loads a value of type float32 as a type F (float) onto the evaluation stack indirectly.

name: Ldind_R8
description: Loads a value of type float64 as a type F (float) onto the evaluation stack indirectly.

name: Ldind_Ref
description: Loads an object reference as a type O (object reference) onto the evaluation stack indirectly.

name: Ldind_U1
description: Loads a value of type unsigned int8 as an int32 onto the evaluation stack indirectly.

name: Ldind_U2
description: Loads a value of type unsigned int16 as an int32 onto the evaluation stack indirectly.

name: Ldind_U4
description: Loads a value of type unsigned int32 as an int32 onto the evaluation stack indirectly.

name: Ldlen
description: Pushes the number of elements of a zero-based, one-dimensional array onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldloc
description: Loads the local variable at a specific index onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldloc
description: Loads the local variable at a specific index onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldloc_0
description: Loads the local variable at index 0 onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldloc_1
description: Loads the local variable at index 1 onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldloc_2
description: Loads the local variable at index 2 onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldloc_3
description: Loads the local variable at index 3 onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldloc_S
description: Loads the local variable at a specific index onto the evaluation stack, short form.

name: Ldloc_S
description: Loads the local variable at a specific index onto the evaluation stack, short form.

name: Ldloca
description: Loads the address of the local variable at a specific index onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldloca_S
description: Loads the address of the local variable at a specific index onto the evaluation stack, short form.

name: Ldnull
description: Pushes a null reference (type O) onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldobj
description: Copies the value type object pointed to by an address to the top of the evaluation stack.

name: Ldsfld
description: Pushes the value of a static field onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldsflda
description: Pushes the address of a static field onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldstr
description: Pushes a new object reference to a string literal stored in the metadata.

name: Ldtoken
description: Converts a metadata token to its runtime representation, pushing it onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldtoken
description: Converts a metadata token to its runtime representation, pushing it onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldtoken
description: Converts a metadata token to its runtime representation, pushing it onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ldvirtftn
description: Pushes an unmanaged pointer (type native int) to the native code implementing a particular virtual method associated with a specified object onto the evaluation stack.

name: Leave
description: Exits a protected region of code, unconditionally transferring control to a specific target instruction.

name: Leave_S
description: Exits a protected region of code, unconditionally transferring control to a target instruction (short form).

name: Localloc
description: Allocates a certain number of bytes from the local dynamic memory pool and pushes the address (a transient pointer, type *) of the first allocated byte onto the evaluation stack.

name: Mkrefany
description: Pushes a typed reference to an instance of a specific type onto the evaluation stack.

name: Mul
description: Multiplies two values and pushes the result on the evaluation stack.

name: Mul_Ovf
description: Multiplies two integer values, performs an overflow check, and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack

name: Mul_Ovf_Un
description: Multiplies two unsigned integer values, performs an overflow check, and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Neg
description: Negates a value and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Newarr
description: Pushes an object reference to a new zero-based, one-dimensional array whose elements are of a specific type onto the evaluation stack.

name: Newobj
description: Creates a new object or a new instance of a value type, pushing an object reference (type O) onto the evaluation stack.

name: Nop
description: Fills space if opcodes are patched. No meaningful operation is performed although a processing cycle can be consumed.

name: Not
description: Computes the bitwise complement of the integer value on top of the stack and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack as the same type.

name: Or
description: Compute the bitwise complement of the two integer values on top of the stack and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Pop
description: Removes the value currently on top of the evaluation stack.

name: Prefix1
description: This is a reserved instruction.

name: Prefix2
description: This is a reserved instruction.

name: Prefix3
description: This is a reserved instruction.

name: Prefix4
description: This is a reserved instruction.

name: Prefix5
description: This is a reserved instruction.

name: Prefix6
description: This is a reserved instruction.

name: Prefix7
description: This is a reserved instruction.

name: Prefixref
description: This is a reserved instruction.

name: Readonly
description: Specifies that the subsequent array address operation performs no type check at run time, and that it returns a managed pointer whose mutability is restricted.

name: Refanytype
description: Retrieves the type token embedded in a typed reference.

name: Refanyval
description: Retrieves the address (type &) embedded in a typed reference.

name: Rem
description: Divides two values and pushes the remainder onto the evaluation stack.

name: Rem_Un
description: Divides two unsigned values and pushes the remainder onto the evaluation stack.

name: Ret
description: Returns from the current method, pushing a return value (if present) from the callee's evaluation stack onto the caller's evaluation stack.

name: Rethrow
description: Rethrows the current exception.

name: Shl
description: Shifts an integer value to the left (in zeroes) by a specified number of bits, pushing the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Shr
description: Shifts an integer value (in sign) to the right by a specified number of bits, pushing the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Shr_Un
description: Shifts an unsigned integer value (in zeroes) to the right by a specified number of bits, pushing the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Sizeof
description: Pushes the size, in bytes, of a supplied value type onto the evaluation stack.

name: Starg
description: Stores the value on top of the evaluation stack in the argument slot at a specified index.

name: Starg_S
description: Stores the value on top of the evaluation stack in the argument slot at a specified index, short form.

name: Stelem
description: Replaces the array element at a given index with the value on the evaluation stack, whose type is specified in the instruction.

name: Stelem_I
description: Replaces the array element at a given index with the native int value on the evaluation stack.

name: Stelem_I1
description: Replaces the array element at a given index with the int8 value on the evaluation stack.

name: Stelem_I2
description: Replaces the array element at a given index with the int16 value on the evaluation stack.

name: Stelem_I4
description: Replaces the array element at a given index with the int32 value on the evaluation stack.

name: Stelem_I8
description: Replaces the array element at a given index with the int64 value on the evaluation stack.

name: Stelem_R4
description: Replaces the array element at a given index with the float32 value on the evaluation stack.

name: Stelem_R8
description: Replaces the array element at a given index with the float64 value on the evaluation stack.

name: Stelem_Ref
description: Replaces the array element at a given index with the object ref value (type O) on the evaluation stack.

name: Stfld
description: Replaces the value stored in the field of an object reference or pointer with a new value.

name: Stind_I
description: Stores a value of type native int at a supplied address.

name: Stind_I1
description: Stores a value of type int8 at a supplied address.

name: Stind_I2
description: Stores a value of type int16 at a supplied address.

name: Stind_I4
description: Stores a value of type int32 at a supplied address.

name: Stind_I8
description: Stores a value of type int64 at a supplied address.

name: Stind_R4
description: Stores a value of type float32 at a supplied address.

name: Stind_R8
description: Stores a value of type float64 at a supplied address.

name: Stind_Ref
description: Stores a object reference value at a supplied address.

name: Stloc
description: Pops the current value from the top of the evaluation stack and stores it in a the local variable list at a specified index.

name: Stloc
description: Pops the current value from the top of the evaluation stack and stores it in a the local variable list at a specified index.

name: Stloc_0
description: Pops the current value from the top of the evaluation stack and stores it in a the local variable list at index 0.

name: Stloc_1
description: Pops the current value from the top of the evaluation stack and stores it in a the local variable list at index 1.

name: Stloc_2
description: Pops the current value from the top of the evaluation stack and stores it in a the local variable list at index 2.

name: Stloc_3
description: Pops the current value from the top of the evaluation stack and stores it in a the local variable list at index 3.

name: Stloc_S
description: Pops the current value from the top of the evaluation stack and stores it in a the local variable list at index (short form).

name: Stloc_S
description: Pops the current value from the top of the evaluation stack and stores it in a the local variable list at index (short form).

name: Stobj
description: Copies a value of a specified type from the evaluation stack into a supplied memory address.

name: Stsfld
description: Replaces the value of a static field with a value from the evaluation stack.

name: Sub
description: Subtracts one value from another and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Sub_Ovf
description: Subtracts one integer value from another, performs an overflow check, and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Sub_Ovf_Un
description: Subtracts one unsigned integer value from another, performs an overflow check, and pushes the result onto the evaluation stack.

name: Switch
description: Implements a jump table.

name: Tailcall
description: Performs a postfixed method call instruction such that the current method's stack frame is removed before the actual call instruction is executed.

name: Throw
description: Throws the exception object currently on the evaluation stack.

name: Unaligned
description: Indicates that an address currently atop the evaluation stack might not be aligned to the natural size of the immediately following ldind, stind, ldfld, stfld, ldobj, stobj, initblk, or cpblk instruction.

name: Unaligned
description: Indicates that an address currently atop the evaluation stack might not be aligned to the natural size of the immediately following ldind, stind, ldfld, stfld, ldobj, stobj, initblk, or cpblk instruction.

name: Unbox
description: Converts the boxed representation of a value type to its unboxed form.

name: Unbox_Any
description: Converts the boxed representation of a type specified in the instruction to its unboxed form.

name: Volatile
description: Specifies that an address currently atop the evaluation stack might be volatile, and the results of reading that location cannot be cached or that multiple stores to that location cannot be suppressed.

name: Xor
description: Computes the bitwise XOR of the top two values on the evaluation stack, pushing the result onto the evaluation stack.
